title: Putting a roof overhead at KID
text: October 8, 2015 Putting a roof overhead at KID Russel Petty, with LCR Construction in Kennewick, works Thursday on the metal roof for the new 15,000-square-foot Kennewick Irrigation District administration building being built at 2015 S. Ely St. in Kennewick. The $2.25 million structure next to KIDâ€™s shop facilities is scheduled to be finished later this winter and the agency is expected to move out of its downtown office by Jan. 1.
